  <description><![CDATA[<p>In the <a data-udi="umb://document/d1bb27ef1cf04b448d45b9dcbfeb2771" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d1bb27ef1cf04b448d45b9dcbfeb2771}" title="Bernese Oberland">Bernese Oberland</a> region of central <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/resorts/switzerland" title="switzerland">Switzerland</a>, this Alpine lake is 17 km long and 3 km wide. A Lake Thun holiday offers you turquoise waters, charming lakeside villages, castles rich in history, rustic mountain farming villages and snow-capped mountains. As with all holidays on the Swiss lakes, a gentle cruise or two on a lake steamer is absolutely essential. The busiest towns are Thun and <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/resorts/switzerland/interlaken" title="interlaken">Interlaken</a> at opposite ends of the lake. Charming Hilterfingen is a small village enjoying a beautiful setting on the northern part of the lake in between Thun and Oberhofen whilst peaceful <a href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/lakes-mountains-holidays/resorts/switzerland/lake-thun/merligen" title="merligen">Merligen</a> is quieter with a few shops and cafes. Both have easy access by bus to the surrounding areas and lake steamers stop regularly for visits to other areas. On your holiday in Lake Thun you will be spoilt for choice for activities, day excursions and walking possibilities.</p>]]></description>
